            of \(5~\rm{fb}^{-1}\) collected by the LHCb experiment. In the \(\Lambda_{c}^{+} K^{-}\) system, the 
            \(\Xi_c(2930)^0\) state observed at the BaBar and Belle experiments is resolved into two narrower states, 
            \(\Xi_c(2923)^0\) and \(\Xi_c(2939)^0\), whose masses and widths are measured to be \(m(\Xi_c(2923)^0) = 
            2924.5 \pm 0.4 \pm 1.1~\rm{MeV}\), \(m(\Xi_c(2939)^0) = 2938.5 \pm 0.9 \pm 2.3~\rm{MeV}\), 
            \(\Gamma(\Xi_c(2923)^0) = 4.8 \pm 0.9 \pm 1.5~\rm{MeV}\), \(\Gamma(\Xi_c(2939)^0) = 11.0 \pm 1.9 \pm 
            7.5~\rm{MeV}\), where the first uncertainties are statistical and the second systematic. The results are 
            consistent with a previous LHCb measurement using a prompt \(\Lambda_{c}^{+} K^{-}\) sample. Evidence of 
            a new \(\Xi_c(2880)^0\) state is found with a local significance of \(3.8\sigma\), whose mass and width 
            are measured to be \(2881.8 \pm 3.1 \pm 8.5~\rm{MeV}\) and \(12.4 \pm 5.3 \pm 5.8~\rm{MeV}\), respectively.
